---

<BaseLayout
  title="90-Day Content Calendar - Admin"
  description="Internal content calendar for ProofLabs — 90-day publishing plan organized by week and priority."
>
  <div class="container-custom" style="padding: 8rem 0 6rem;">
    <div style="max-width: 72rem; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="background-color: #fef3c7; border: 2px solid #f59e0b; border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        <h2 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: #92400e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
          🔒 Internal Page - Not Public
        </h2>
        <p style="color: #78350f; margin: 0;">
          This page is for Tyler and Vi only. It's not linked from the public navigation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h1 style="font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 900; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        90-Day Content Calendar
      </h1>
      
      <p style="font-size: 1.125rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
        Complete publishing plan for ProofLabs. 30 articles organized by priority and week. P1 = highest affiliate value and Tyler's unique expertise.
      </p>

      {calendar.map((phase, idx) => (
        <div style="margin-bottom: 4rem;">
          <h2 style="font-size: 1.75rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--color-text); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 0.5rem;">
            {phase.week}
          </h2>
          
          <div style="display: grid; gap: 1.5rem;">
            {phase.articles.map((article, articleIdx) => (
              <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 1.5rem;">
                <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: start; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                  <div style="flex: 1;">
                    <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                      <span style={`font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); background-color: ${article.priority === 'P1' ? '#dbeafe' : article.priority === 'P2' ? '#fef3c7' : '#f3f4f6'}; color: ${article.priority === 'P1' ? '#1e40af' : article.priority === 'P2' ? '#92400e' : '#374151'};`}>
                        {article.priority}
                      </span>
                      <span style="font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); background-color: #f3f4f6; color: #6b7280;">
                        {article.status}
                      </span>
                      <span style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-light);">
                        {article.words} words
                      </span>
                    </div>
                    <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                      {articleIdx + 1 + (idx > 0 ? calendar.slice(0, idx).reduce((sum, p) => sum + p.articles.length, 0) : 0)}. {article.title}
                    </h3>
                    <code style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-secondary); background-color: var(--color-secondary-bg); padding: 0.25rem 0.5rem; border-radius: var(--radius-sm); display: inline-block; margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                      {article.url}
                    </code>
                    <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.5rem;">
                      <strong>Primary keyword:</strong> {article.primaryKW}
                    </p>
                    {article.notes && (
                      <p style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text-light); font-style: italic;">
                        {article.notes}
                      </p>
                    )}
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}

      <hr style="border: 0; border-top: 2px solid var(--color-border); margin: 4rem 0;" />

      <h2 style="font-size: 2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--color-text);">
        Content Templates
      </h2>

      <div style="display: grid; gap: 2rem;">
        <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">
            "Best X for Y" Roundup Template
          </h3>
          <ol style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>H1: Best Credit Card for [Category] in 2026</li>
            <li>Author byline + last updated date</li>
            <li>Bold "Bottom Line" summary (2-3 sentences, names the winner)</li>
            <li>Quick comparison table (top 3 cards: Card Name | Rewards Rate | Annual Fee | Best For)</li>
            <li>Tyler's Tip mascot callout (personal experience with this category)</li>
            <li>Detailed analysis for each card (Why it wins / competitive / made the list)</li>
            <li>Profit calculation with real spending scenarios</li>
            <li>Methodology section (brief, links to /methodology)</li>
            <li>FAQ section (5 questions, unique answers, FAQ schema)</li>
            <li>Related articles (2-3 links to comparisons, educational content, other categories)</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">
            Head-to-Head Comparison Template
          </h3>
          <ol style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>H1: [Card A] vs [Card B]</li>
            <li>Author byline + last updated</li>
            <li>"Choose [Card A] if…" / "Choose [Card B] if…" decision box</li>
            <li>Side-by-side comparison table (every spec)</li>
            <li>Category-by-category spending scenario breakdown</li>
            <li>Tyler's Pick mascot callout (which one Tyler would choose and why)</li>
            <li>FAQ section</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">
            Individual Review Template
          </h3>
          <ol style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>H1: [Card Name] Review 2026</li>
            <li>Author byline + last updated</li>
            <li>Pros/Cons box</li>
            <li>Key specs table</li>
            <li>Who this card is for / Who it's NOT for</li>
            <li>Rewards structure deep dive with math</li>
            <li>Tyler's experience (if he uses/has used the card)</li>
            <li>Comparison to alternatives</li>
            <li>FAQ section</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: var(--color-surface); border: 1px solid var(--color-border-light); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--color-text);">
            Strategy Guide Template
          </h3>
          <ol style="color: var(--color-text-muted); padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
            <li>H1: How to [Strategy]</li>
            <li>Author byline</li>
            <li>Tyler's result callout ("I earned $X/year using this strategy")</li>
            <li>Step-by-step numbered guide</li>
            <li>Tools/apps needed</li>
            <li>Real example with Tyler's numbers</li>
            <li>Common mistakes section</li>
            <li>MascotTip callouts throughout</li>
            <li>Related strategies and card recommendations</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="background-color: var(--color-secondary-bg); border-left: 4px solid #0284c7; padding: 2rem; margin-top: 3rem; border-radius: var(--radius-md);">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-secondary-dark);">
          <strong>Note:</strong> All articles should show Tyler's real numbers, personal experience, and math. This is what separates ProofLabs from NerdWallet/Bankrate.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
